  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Student Services Administrative Assistant",
  "description": "<h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><p><strong>Student & Frontline Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Assist students, parents, and staff with enquiries via phone, email, and in person</p></li><li><p>Perform front office duties, including greeting visitors and providing accurate information</p></li><li><p>Manage incoming calls and oversee the centre’s mobile phone</p></li></ul><p><strong>Administrative & Records Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain and update student and parent records, including:</p><ul><li><p>Enrolment and withdrawal processes</p></li><li><p>Subsidy matters (e.g. SCFA)</p></li><li><p>Daily student attendance tracking</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Maintain accurate academic and financial records</p></li><li><p>Manage filing systems and ensure proper document storage</p></li><li><p>Regularly update student listings and centre databases</p></li></ul><p><strong>Admissions & Centre Operations</strong></p><ul><li><p>Schedule and coordinate new enquiries and centre visits</p></li><li><p>Support recruitment, admissions, and graduation-related activities</p></li><li><p>Assist with administrative planning and student services projects</p></li></ul><p><strong>Logistics, Coordination & Communications</strong></p><ul><li><p>Coordinate with vendors for centre operational needs</p></li><li><p>Order and manage uniform stock and office supplies</p></li><li><p>Support and coordinate centre events or meetings</p></li><li><p>Manage the centre’s social media accounts and create digital flyers</p></li></ul><p><strong>Compliance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure adherence to school policies and data protection regulations</p></li></ul><p><strong>Other Duties</strong></p><ul><li><p>Perform any other duties as assigned by the Centre Manager</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><ul><li><p>GCE ‘O’ Level or above</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications</p></li><li><p>Experience in administrative and/or student care roles preferred</p></li><li><p>Good communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to multitask and work independently</p></li><li><p>Responsible, organised, and detail-oriented</p></li><li><p>Enjoy working with children</p></li></ul><p><strong>Please send your resume to:</strong> <a href=\"#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">hopescc@plmc.org</a></p>",
